---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base
  title="Writing"
  description="Selected papers and writeups by John Abrahams — systems, applied ML, and clinical research."
  current="writing"
>
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <span class="eyebrow">Writing</span>
      <h1 class="display display-md writing-h1">Papers &amp; writeups.</h1>
      <p class="lead writing-lead">
        A short list. The systems work and the clinical work usually share an
        author with someone smarter than me; the academic work occasionally
        does too.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section-tight">
    <div class="container">
      <article class="entry">
        <header class="entry-head">
          <h2 class="entry-title">
            <a href="/papers/khronos.pdf" target="_blank" rel="noopener">
              Khronos: A Type II Exovisor Architecture with WebAssembly
            </a>
          </h2>
          <span class="mono entry-meta">2025 · with Ajax Li · IEEE format · 9 pp.</span>
        </header>
        <p class="entry-blurb">
          A multi-tenant WebAssembly runtime that combines language-level
          sandboxing with exokernel-style capability gating and a custom
          <code>wasi:thread-spawn</code> dispatcher. ~5,000 lines of Rust;
          ~0.08&nbsp;MiB per isolate (3× denser than Wasmtime, 18× denser than
          Docker); up to 6.7× speedup on dense matrix multiply while
          preserving per-tenant trap containment.
        </p>
        <p class="entry-links">
          <a href="/projects/khronos">Project page</a>
          <span aria-hidden="true">·</span>
          <a href="/papers/khronos.pdf" target="_blank" rel="noopener">PDF ↗</a>
          <span aria-hidden="true">·</span>
          <a href="https://github.com/jca225/webAssembly_Interpreter" target="_blank" rel="noopener">GitHub ↗</a>
        </p>
      </article>

      <article class="entry">
        <header class="entry-head">
          <h2 class="entry-title">
            <a href="/papers/zimvie-acdf-predictive-modeling.pdf" target="_blank" rel="noopener">
              A Single-Neurosurgeon Experience with the ZimVie LDR-C ROI Implant: A Study of 236 Patients with Predictive Outcome Modeling
            </a>
          </h2>
          <span class="mono entry-meta">2024 · co-author · 236-patient cohort</span>
        </header>
        <p class="entry-blurb">
          Predictive outcome modeling after Anterior Cervical Diskectomy &amp;
          Fusion. Evaluated EM-algorithm and regression-based imputation for
          missing covariates, then fit logistic regression and SVMs to
          predict patient outcomes from preoperative features. Co-authored
          while a research associate at New York Brain &amp; Spine Surgery.
        </p>
        <p class="entry-links">
          <a href="/papers/zimvie-acdf-predictive-modeling.pdf" target="_blank" rel="noopener">PDF ↗</a>
        </p>
      </article>

      <article class="entry">
        <header class="entry-head">
          <h2 class="entry-title">
            <a href="/papers/gradient-descent-analysis.pdf" target="_blank" rel="noopener">
              Gradient Descent Analysis
            </a>
          </h2>
          <span class="mono entry-meta">2023 · with Prof. Arielle Carr · Lehigh</span>
        </header>
        <p class="entry-blurb">
          A short technical writeup on gradient-descent dynamics for a class
          of optimisation problems we worked through with Prof.&nbsp;Carr.
          The paper develops the convergence-rate analysis carefully and
          checks it against numerical experiments.
        </p>
        <p class="entry-links">
          <a href="/papers/gradient-descent-analysis.pdf" target="_blank" rel="noopener">PDF ↗</a>
        </p>
      </article>

      <article class="entry">
        <header class="entry-head">
          <h2 class="entry-title">
            <a href="/papers/highlighting-algorithm.pdf" target="_blank" rel="noopener">
              A Highlighting Algorithm for Document Search
            </a>
          </h2>
          <span class="mono entry-meta">2024 · capstone writeup · Lehigh CSE</span>
        </header>
        <p class="entry-blurb">
          The sentence-level highlight extractor at the heart of my Lehigh
          capstone search engine. Given a query and a matched sentence,
          surface the minimal sub-span that explains the match. This is
          deceptively non-trivial when the query is multi-word, partially
          stop-worded, or syntactically interleaved with the matched
          sentence.
        </p>
        <p class="entry-links">
          <a href="/projects/capstone-search">Project page</a>
          <span aria-hidden="true">·</span>
          <a href="/papers/highlighting-algorithm.pdf" target="_blank" rel="noopener">PDF ↗</a>
        </p>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>
</Base>

<style>
  .writing-h1 { margin-top: 0.6rem; }
  .writing-lead { margin-top: 1.5rem; max-width: 56ch; color: var(--ink-muted); }

  .entry {
    border-top: 1px solid var(--rule);
    padding-block: 2rem;
  }
  .entry:last-child { border-bottom: 1px solid var(--rule); }
  .entry-head {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.4rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.8rem;
  }
  .entry-title {
    font-family: var(--font-serif);
    font-size: clamp(1.3rem, 2.2vw, 1.6rem);
    font-weight: 400;
    letter-spacing: -0.015em;
    line-height: 1.25;
  }
  .entry-title a { border: none; }
  .entry-title a:hover { color: var(--accent); }
  .entry-meta {
    font-size: 0.72rem;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    color: var(--ink-muted);
  }
  .entry-blurb {
    color: var(--ink);
    max-width: 64ch;
    font-size: 1rem;
  }
  .entry-blurb code {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.86em;
    background: var(--bg-subtle);
    padding: 0.1em 0.35em;
    border-radius: 3px;
  }
  .entry-links {
    margin-top: 0.7rem;
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.78rem;
    color: var(--ink-muted);
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: 0.5rem;
    align-items: center;
  }
  .entry-links a { color: var(--ink); border-bottom: 1px solid var(--rule-strong); padding-bottom: 1px; }
  .entry-links a:hover { color: var(--accent); border-bottom-color: var(--accent); }
</style>
